cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the performance of FIFO queues over wireless networks and proposes a resource allocation scheme and scheduling algorithm for the same. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper characterizes the stability region of the system and develops an inner-bound on it. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper proposes a stochastic flow control and scheduling algorithm for the system. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with improving the throughput of wireless networks, which is relevant for multimedia applications. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) is another possible category as the paper proposes algorithms to improve the performance of wireless networks with FIFO queues.
